Preheat your oven to 200°C and boil your #kettle{}. Put the @Skin-On British Chicken Breasts{2}, skin-side up, on a #baking tray{} and drizzle with @oil{1%splash}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} then roast in your oven until golden and cooked through, ~{16-18%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, chop the @Salad Potatoes{350%g} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel) and pop into a #saucepan{} with a @salt{pinch}. Pour on the boiling water and put the pan on high heat. Boil until tender, ~{12-15%minutes}, then drain into a #colander{}. Return to the pan and add the @Flora and stir to melt.

Trim the root and dark green leafy part from the @Leek{2}. Halve lengthways then slice widthways. Pick the @Tarragon{1/2} leaves from their stalks and roughly chop (discard the stalks).

Heat a splash of @oil{1%splash} in a #frying pan{} on medium heat. Add the leek and cook, stirring, until soft, ~{5-6%minutes}. Add the @Water for the Sauce{50} and @Chicken Stock Powder{1/2}. Bring to the boil, stir to dissolve the stock powder, then reduce the heat to low.

Stir the @Creme Fraiche{150%g} and half the tarragon into the leek mixture. Remove from the heat. Season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Slice the chicken. Serve the potatoes alongside the chicken. Top with the leek and tarragon sauce and finish with a sprinkling of remaining tarragon. Enjoy!